<!-- description -->


comment is piece of code which is ignored by any web browser.

comments do not nest which means a comment cannot be put inside another comment.
the double-dash sequence "--" may not appear inside a comment except as part of closing --> tag.


multiline comments

conditional comments
conditional comments only work in Internet Explorer (IE) on windows but they are ignored by other browsers.
they are supported from Explorer 5 onwards, and you can use them to give conditional instruction to different versions of IE.
<!-- [if IE 6]>
	special instructions fo rIE 6 here
<![endif]-->



//ref
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/html/html_comments.htm
